<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. F. Lu, W. Y. Xie &amp; X. F. Jin" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Cerastium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cerastium huadingense" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="huadingense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Cerastium huadingense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
' refers to the type locality of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
Vulnerable, VU B2ab(iii)C1 (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Central China Normal University" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" publicationUrl="https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" refId="B7" refString="IUCN, 2019. Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" title="Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee." url="https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
). The new species is only known from two localities, Mount Huading in Tiantai and Mount Siming in Yuyao, and occupied less than 400 km2 with about 5000 mature individuals. This species is considered as Vulnerable (VU) according to IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Central China Normal University" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" publicationUrl="https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" refId="B7" refString="IUCN, 2019. Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" title="Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee." url="https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
) based on the current data.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
